              "q": "Using Huygens' wave theory, derive Snell's law of refraction.",
              "explain": "Model answer: A plane wavefront AB of light hits boundary at angle i. By time wavelet from B reaches B' on the boundary (BB'=v₁t), wavelet from A travels v₂t into denser medium. Geometry: sin i / sin r = v₁/v₂ = n₂/n₁ (constant). This is Snell's law.",
