        "heading": "10.5 Diffraction of Light",
        "body": "<p>10.5 Diffraction of Light</p><p>The locus of all the particle, which oscillate in same phase is called wavefront.</p><ul><li>A line perpendicular at any point an wavefront represent the direction of propagation.</li></ul><ul><li>This perpendicular line is called a ray. The wavefront can be of different shapes, depending on the shape of source of light wavefront can be of three types, which are given below,</li></ul><p>(i) Spherical wavefront When the source of light is a point source, the wavefront is spherical. W YOUR PRACTICE GOAL - Objective Type Questions (32 Qs; MCQs, A-R, Matching) - Case Based Questions-2</p><p>- Subjective Questions (7 VSAs, 8 SAs, 9 LAs) - Numerical Problems-9</p><p>Wavefronts</p><p>(ii) Cylindrical wavefront When the source of light is linear, e.g. a straight line source, slit etc. as shown in the figure.</p><p>instant of time gives the new wavefront at that instant. This is called secondary wavefront. '1</p><p>A2 82 Wavefront</p><p>s</p><p>D2</p><p>Propagation of light wave</p><p>'2</p><p>All the points equidistant from the source lie on a cylinder. Therefore, the wavefront is produced cylindrical in shape, (hi) Plane wavefront When the point source or linear source of light is at very large distance, the</p><p>wavefront appears to be plane, known as a plane wavefront.</p><p>In Fig.(a), F, Fj is the section of the given spherical wavefront and Gj G2 is the new wavefront in the forward direction. In Fig.(b). ,F Fj is the section of the given plane wavefront and GjGj is the new wavefront in the forward direction.</p><p>^TEACHER TIP The amplitude of the secondary wavelets is maximum in the forward direction and zero in the backward direction. Hence,</p><p>the backward secondary wavefront is absent. Light rays Plane wavefronts</p>",
