              "prompt": "Why did Rutherford conclude the atom's positive charge is concentrated at the centre?",
              "steps": [
                "Most $\\alpha$ particles passed undeflected through the gold foil — atom is mostly empty.",
                "A small fraction were deflected through large angles, even backward.",
                "Such large deflections require a strong, concentrated repulsive force, hence a tiny massive positive nucleus."
              ],
              "finalAnswer": "Large-angle scattering of a few $\\alpha$ particles required a tiny dense positive nucleus.",
              "_source": "Authored from NCERT/ISC pattern"
