        "heading": "12.5 Hydrogen Spectrum or Line",
        "body": "<p>12.5 Hydrogen Spectrum or Line Spectra of Hydrogen Atom Hydrogen spectrum consists of discrete bright lines in a dark background and it is specifically known as hydrogen emission spectrum.There is one more type of hydrogen spectrum that exists where we get dark</p><p>Balmer Series in Emission Spectrum of Hydrogen In Balmer series, the spectral line with the longest wavelength {656.3 nm) in red region is called H^. Next line with wavelength 486,1 nm in blue-green region is</p><p>called Hpi the third line with 434.1 nm in violet region and is called H.^ and so on. As the wavelength decreases, the lines are weaker in intensity and appear closer together.</p>",
