              "id": "we_phys_13_T21_1",
              "prompt": "Why does fusion require very high temperatures?",
              "steps": [
                "Both nuclei are positive — to fuse they must approach within nuclear-force range (~few fm).",
                "They must overcome the Coulomb repulsion barrier (MeV-scale).",
                "High temperature provides the thermal kinetic energy needed to penetrate the barrier."
              ],
              "finalAnswer": "Thermal energies (~keV–MeV) are needed to overcome Coulomb repulsion.",
              "_source": "Authored from NCERT/ISC pattern"
